## CI Gates

All PRs must pass in this order:
1. [ ] Lint (fast fail)
2. [ ] Type check (if applicable)
3. [ ] Unit tests
4. [ ] Integration tests
5. [ ] Coverage threshold check
{{- if .HasProfile}}
{{- if .Profile.QA.E2E}}
6. [ ] E2E tests (on merge to main only)
{{- end}}
{{- end}}

## Test Writing Rules

- Tests live alongside source code (`_test.go`, `*.test.ts`, `test_*.py`)
- No mocking of the database in integration tests — use {{- if .HasProfile}} {{.Profile.QA.Integration}}{{- else}} real containers{{- end}}
- Every bug fix includes a regression test
- Test names describe behavior, not implementation (`TestCharge_DeclinedCard`, not `TestChargeFunc3`)

## Anti-Patterns

- Do not skip tests with `t.Skip()` / `it.skip()` without a linked ticket
- Do not use `time.Sleep` in tests — use retry loops or event-driven assertions
- Do not assert on exact timestamps — use time windows

